ASUS has unveiled its new ROG Strix GL504 Scar II and Hero II gaming laptops, which sport a narrow-bezel design and slimmer frames. Both products are available with 15.6-inch Full HD displays that boast aÂ 144Hz refresh rate, and Intel Core i7-8750H processors. The ASUS ROG Strix Scar II can support an Nvidia GeForce GTX 1070, while the Strix Hero II features a GeForce GTX 1060 6GB. The devices share the same chassis and overall design, and both include RGB keyboards paired with dual-speaker systems. There is currently no pricing information available for the Scar II and Hero II, but the devices are set to launch later this year. The maximum specifications for the new ASUS ROG Strix laptops are below.